			<ns0:name>eaelt...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/103360015124260446450/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">For x86 tools, we are currently using target alias nacl for i686 and nacl64 for x86_64. Thus the tools are named like: nacl64-gcc, nacl-as, etc.

These target aliases are &amp;quot;wrong&amp;quot; - they are not consistent with what is usually used for gnu tools. If we introduce more architectures that support nacl, we probably can&#8217;t suggest a consistent target naming scheme that keeps the existing aliases.

We need to use &amp;quot;better&amp;quot; names.

Full canonical triplet for i686 is i686-pc-nacl. Full canonical triplet for x86_64 is x86_64-pc-nacl. I don't see direct benefits of using full triplets, so the plan is to use abbreviated target aliases, i686-nacl and x86_64-nacl.

Here are examples of old and new tools names:
nacl-gcc -&amp;gt; i686-nacl-gcc
nacl64-gcc -&amp;gt; x86_64-nacl-gcc
